pr_review_comment_body:
@pedrobaeza you need that add "if" to all method, because all query has "module" field. In other words:
if not release.version_info[0] > 7:
    return
(Before "for")

To overcome the issue caused by hardware acceleration, we may have some options:
1. support atomic operation in hardware [AES implementation](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/master/third_party/NordicSemiconductor/libraries/crypto/hw/aes_alt_cc310.c);
2. implement another software version AES which is not based on mbedtls;
3. don't use hardware acceleration when enable time sync feature.

May I know your opinion? Any suggestions would be appreciated.

Cool. I hadn't used `LocalProxy` before.

I will look into modifying `invenio/ext/logging/__init__.py:deprecated` to work with the new deprecation warning classes and then it should be a little more organized:

```python
@deprecated('Use the other variables instead', (2, 2))
@property
def cfg_prefix():
    return distutils.sysconfig.get_config_var("prefix")
CFG_PREFIX = LocalProxy(cfg_prefix)
